ğŸ” OPSEC Thoughts
Pro: Very stealthy if you already have SSH access

Con: If your iptables changes get logged/monitored, it may raise flags on the pivot box

ğŸ”¥ Real World or CPTS Use?
âœ… Great for CPTS labs: fast setup, no proxychains jank, clean output

âš ï¸ Real world: works best when youâ€™ve got legit SSH access (not always the case), and may not scale well compared to socks proxies and pivot tools


